HEADWORD: Bikh
<hw>Bikh</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Hind., fr. Skr.
<ets>visha</ets> poison.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The East Indian
name of a virulent poison extracted from <spn>Aconitum ferox</spn> or
other species of aconite: also, the plant itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

